adjectives.description: objectable (comparative more objectable, superlative most objectable)

entries.meaning: (rare, possibly archaic) Capable of being put forward as an objection.
examples: It is as objectable against all those things which either native beauty or art affords.

entries.meaning: (rare) Capable of being made into or treated as an object (especially by a computer program or programming language).

examples: Nothing surely which they did, was more objectable than their Proceedings against Magdalen College[.]
